latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Spooky Season is in full swing, and I’m testing out, swatching, and reviewing the Limited Edition Halloween Collection by @milanicosmetics . If you’re interested in affordable makeup for October, be sure to watch and let me know if you pick up anything. Also, I forgot to mention why I apply my eyeshadow after mascara and eyeliner, but I have found it works best for me and my hooded eye problems. I like to create my wing first, as a way to navigate where to place the shadow, and I also find that liner applies more opaque without shadow down first. And, then I just go back over it after the shadow is applied. I know it’s unorthodox, but it works for me. 
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Mental Health Monday Body Image Story
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Growing up as a “chubby” somewhat overweight kid, I became consumed with food and body image issues at a very young age. This is my story revealing the dangerous path that obsession took me down, and how I recovered serval years ago. I wish IGTV could be 30 minutes; because, I didn’t even get into how all shapes and sizes of bodies inspire me now, and how I wish we wouldn’t compare ourselves so much. I think it starts with self love and affirmations daily, telling yourself, “this is the body I have been given. My body is precious. My body is just as valuable as the Body next to me, or across the world from me, in a magazine or on a runway. I get one shot at treating it right. And, I’m going to nourish it and cherish it as a sacred gift.” I believe that sharing our stories is the most powerful way to open dialogue and safe havens for others who are currently in the thick of their struggles. Silence is a deafening enemy. A thief of progress. A muffler of truth. I hope that by sharing my story, someone will feel safe enough to reach out for help, whether it be body dysmorphia, self hate, drug or alcohol addiction, depression, abuse, etc. There is no shame in admitting your struggles. That’s strength. That’s bravery. And, it’s never to late to get help. My Dms are always open. 
.
.

Heart: Woody Coumarin, Jasmine

✨ Not only is the bottle gorgeous, but the juice inside is even more beautiful on the skin. @blakebrownbeauty has joined the growing popularity of Hair and Body mists with three on-the-go layerable scents: Wild Nectar Santal, Sandalwood Vanille, and Bergamot Woods. 

✨ One thing that I like about these particular mists is that that don’t leave my hair crunchy like some other brands. A few seconds after dry down, my hair feels soft and like its normal state. I also think all three scents make sense as hair fragrances, while some other brands’ scents aren’t my preferred hair scent style. 

✨At $18.99 at @Target or $19.00 on Blake Brown’s site, for 5ml, I think that’s a very reasonable price. The lasting power is in line with most body and hair mists for me, which is about 2-3 hours. I don’t expect longer than that for what they are, and they are meant to be take with you to refresh. 
.
✨ I rank them in the order that I show in the reel. If you didn’t watch it all the way through, you’ll have to go back and do that to know that that order is.

I’m enamored with @fultonandroark Calle Ocho, and obviously, intoxicated by it, as well. It’s also a fragrance that was a very strong like at first sniff, but after wearing it several days, it’s a huge love for me. 
.
❤️ I failed to mention tobacco as a note within the reel, and I actually think the tobacco leaf is what gives Calle Ocho more rich, smooth depth than other fragrances with a similar vibe. I can think of one in particular that rivals Calle Ocho, but as much as I love that one, I love this one more. It’s kind of like sampling two fine wines and one goes down a little smoother. 
.
❤️TOP NOTES:
Cinnamon, Rum & Bitter Chocolate

MID NOTES:
Night-blooming Jasmine, Labdanum & Tobacco Leaf

BASE NOTES:
Tonka Bean, Sandalwood & Musk

❤️ I also love that as strong and long lasting Calle Ocho is, it never comes off as oppressive or cloying. It has a quiet strength that exudes elegance and class. 
.
❤️ I love that Fulton and Roark offers discovery sets, that include a $30 off full size bottle, so that you can ensure the commitment will be satisfactory. Although they are on the higher end price wise, you only need one or two sprays for the entire day. These bottles will last you a long time. 

* Kindly gifted

Understated cozy elegance describes @rosyandearnest Be Rosy in the most simplistic terms; although, I could go on superfluously. I tend to do that sometimes, but only; because, I’m passionate about what I love. And, I love Be Rosy! 
.
✨ Much like the other Rosy & Earnest offerings, Be Rosy doesn’t have to be boastful to be adored and noticed. Its power is in its subtle and soft embrace. You don’t want it to let you go. Be Rosy feels like a sun warmed cardigan draped across your shoulders. It invites you to wrap it around you closely and nuzzle into its unassuming softness. It smells as cashmere feels, silky and delicately cozy. A scent you’d wear cuddled up with your favorite blanket and a book you want to be lost in, sitting in a window chair, sun seeping through the shades and warming your skin. It doesn’t matter if someone else in the room can smell it. You can. And, that’s all you need it to be. 

✨ Notes include italian clementine oil, french carrot oil, pear accord, osmanthus absolute, orris butter, black tea CO2, cedarwood, ambrox and musk. *Synthetic Notes: Rosy & Earnest fragrances do not use animal products and are EWG verified.

The latest @elysianparfums bottle to cross off my wish list! Coco & Capri. 
.
🌊 During Winter, I ranked Coco & Capri in my tops of the Lineage Collection, and had been waiting to pull the trigger, as it truly smells like freshly squeezed Summer in a bottle. And, now I get to enjoy it in its intended climate and season. 
.
☀️Notes: marine, ozone, sun-dried linens, fresh pear, juicy pineapple, coconut, birch, exotic jasmine, sandalwood tropical woods, white musk

🌊 Interestingly, I don’t pick up coconut near as much as I pick up an almost green pineapple pear pairing that reads as limey to my nose. It comes across as a burst of tropical citrus, followed by waves of fresh ozonic marine notes, and softened by that subtle fresh linen… like you were blasted with bright fruity infused ocean water and now hanging out to dry in the clean coastal air. It’s simultaneously refreshing and invigorating while calming in the dry down. A perfect hot Summer day fragrance, and also perfectly unisex, in my opinion. 
.
☀️ Now to continue marking off my Elysian wishlist. It’s a long one! 
.
